name: kansas-satellite-image-database-ksid-2004-2005
notes: The Kansas Satellite Image Database (KSID) 2004-2005 consists of terrain-corrected, precision rectified spring, summer, and fall Landsat 5 Thematic Mapper (TM) imagery covering the state of Kansas that has been tiled by county and is in GeoTiff format. Although some county triplicates date wholly from either 2004 or 2005, some county triplicates were constructed using imagery from both 2004 and 2005. The KSID: 2004-2005 consists of raw data and visual products. The raw dataset consists of the seven geometrically corrected Landsat 5 bands in their original units (DN values). The visual dataset consists of three products: Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) images, false- color infrared composites, and resolution-enhanced natural color composites.
